l Jewish communities of early modern Europe, and was influential through his extraordinary work as a printer and his efforts on behalf of the readmission of Jews to England. In this lively biography, Steven Nadler provides a fresh perspective on this seminal figure.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCrypto-JewszIberian PeninsulaxHistoryy16th century. 0aHebrew imprintsxPublishingzNetherlandszAmsterdamxHistoryy17th century. 0aJewish printerszNetherlandszAmsterdamvBiography. 0aJewszNetherlandszAmsterdamxHistoryy17th century. 0aJudaismzNetherlandszAmsterdamxHistoryy17th century. 0aPrintingzNetherlandszAmsterdamxHistoryy17th century. 0aRabbiszNetherlandszAmsterdamvBiography. 0aSephardimzNetherlandszAmsterdamvBiography. 0aSephardimzNetherlandszAmsterdamxHistoryy17th century. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Religious.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030024043640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300240436423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300240436/original  a978-3-11-063899-8  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles